Nomad Chef - Season 1, Episode 8




Belize

Deep in the jungles of Belize, Jock attempts to unlock the culinary secrets of the descendants of ancient Mayans. He hits the country's Caribbean coast to cook up a storm with a unique Afro-Caribbean people descended from indigenous Arawaks and African slaves, freedives for conch, goes hunting for rodents and discovers that chocolate really does grow on trees when he explores two resilient cuisines that have withstood the onslaught of colonialism and slavery.




Original Air Date: 13-Dec-2014
